caption: Staff is friendly. The food, not so great. I truly don’t write bad reviews unless I really feel ripped off. We ordered take out, the curry was watery, the rice was literally mush. That’s on top of the little food they give you while charging full price. Avoid this place if you don’t like wasting money.  Truly disappointed.
First time here with a friend. Thoroughly enjoyed it and will definitely be back
Great food! Great Staff! I would highly recommend if your looking for great Thai food. It’s a hidden gem on Taylor and I’m glad I ordered. I will definitely be going back sooner than later.
This place used to be great. It’s now just ok but better than most anyplace else around here. Tom Kar and Tom Yum soups are good as long as the chicken is good. It can be unpredictable.
Good prices, will need to try some other dishes, green curry was fine.
Vary good food and service
Been ordering from Golden Thai for several years. Never disappointed, except when they aren't open.
Honestly this is an incredible spot for the best Thai food. I went back the next day because I liked it so much. The staff is friendly and the food is ready very quickly.
Used to go here all the time till they stop taking my American Express
God food, great service!
best thai takeout and delivery in the city
Amazing and authentic food! Best Tom Yum soup I’ve ever had and very friendly staff.

We came to this spot for dinner. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was very successful. The crew were very polite and we had a great feeling. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we shall definitely come back again. We recommend this place to all.
Worse customer service! They gave me the wrong food and the lady began yelling like it's my fault.. im tired of dealing with this lady and her rude as attitude
The place never fails me. I love the staff I love the food just a great place all around.

SO!!!# TODAY WAS MY VERY FIRST TIME COMING HERE AND EATING THERE FOOD... AND I MUST SAY THAT THIS IS THE BEST THAI FOOD I'VE HAD IN VERY LONG TIME. SORRY IT TOOK quarantine for me to find this fabulous food of theirs. I'm definitely coming back and back and back!!! 😆... Seriously tho... This is really good and the customer service is amazing. I did not get the lady that was taking/serving the orders name!!! Wish i had😢😢... But she was so nice and kind and very welcoming!! And she also handed me some HAND SANITIZER after i was finished signing and grabbing my order.... Amazing amazing!!! Thank you!!!

I adore this place! They prepare superb meals, their menu is varied, The chief cook in that place is an expert, I enjoy a lot trying all their food. The dishes are always fresh and tasty, the attitude towards the visitors  is nice. I visit often this place and I not even once was disappointed. I recommend it with no hesitation.
Every time when we visit this restaurant,  is the best experience in the zone, my family love this place. Excellent foot and service
great food and service
Intimate restaurant. Great staff. Went with my coworkers on our lunch break.
I love Thai and this place is just as good.  Fast service, very polite and a nice little place for a quick bite.
Great lunch spot. I love the panang curry. The shumai are also good.

This has to be a no-nonsense, all taste Thai place. A hit with UIC students, it offers a wide variety of authentic Thai dishes with medium to spicy options. Plenty of options that can be customized to cater to vegetarian. Special shout-out to the Indian curry fried rice!

This is my favorite Thai food place. The service is fast and friendly and the food is very good. This place is always consistently good. Soups and pad Thai are my favorite. I love how they serve hot jasmine tea in clear glass mugs. Traditional Thai decorations on the wall add to the overall Thai restaurant appeal. Also, the bathrooms are mice and clean.
Best Pad See Ew!
Best Pad See Ew in town, lots of beef and broccoli!

Really like this place! I got wonton soup, Singapore noodle and coconut custard. The soup was okay and was a good pair with the noodle. The noodle is so well spiced and I just couldn’t stop eating! The coconut custard is right at the pleasant level of sweetness. Will definitely visit again!

Best Thai place in medical district area. The indian curry fried rice is amazing but really you can pick anything on their menu and you will be  satisfied. We would almost eat here every week when we lived on taylor st.
Nice food. Service is sometimes good, sometimes really bad.

Good food. Large portions with reasonable price. Very friendly staff. I highly recommend.

Overall Golden Thai was ok. The positives are that the portions were a good size and the price was around $10 a plate. I gave it only three stars because my Basil Chicken had hardly any basil in it and wasnt nearly as good as other thai basil Ive had. It also had very little vegetables.  Also, the chicken meat was strange. Rather than sliced up chicken it was more like ground chicken. It was kind of a weird texture that i didnt love. We also ordered pad thai. It was good, but lacked the normal pad thai taste. There were no peanuts and didnt have the normal flavoring we have usually experienced. This didnt effect my rating but i did get it a medium heat level. That wasnt very spicy. Maybe like a medium salsa. Definitely less heat than a jalapeno.
My favorite Thai place in the city

Casual dining place with very nice dishes. I love the panang curry -- it is on the sweeter side but you can add your own spices as well. I am vegan and I really enjoy their fried crispy tofu as the protein option. Their drunken noodles are another great choice for vegan/vegetarians.
love this place, my first time there, will be going back.  great portions, yummy food, amazing staff that made sure my family and I where comfortable.  great prices
Nice dishes. VISA/Mastercard only.
Amazing food and really good service! Highly recommend the red curry and pad see ew.

Very good Thai food. I usually ask for medium level of spiciness in my dishes. Be aware that the spiciness is hotter here. Love the atmosphere and staff. You can also bring your own beverage, which always saves me a couple dollars.
So good
Great food, reasonable price.
Loved my curry and baby egg rolls. Service was fast and courteous. Enjoyed the small restaurant. I would definitely return and I would encourage you to give them a try.
Try the Panang Curry! Worth it.

I love their food. I used to order from here all the time because they are super quick and accurate. Their inhouse service is great too. P.S: They need to add the fortune cookie with the delivery too.
The menu is very well-priced. This is a great place to go with a friend or a date and order a couple of entrees, some appetizers, and hot tea to share while still spending less than $30.

Very calming environment, and food was scrumptious.

Food is delicious. Pricing is fair. I got the drunken noodles with beef and it was delicious. The serving size is moderate, slightly smaller than other Thai restaurants I have been too. The noodles were cooked well; soft and not chewy. The meat was delicious and flavorful. The dish was spicy and flavorful. The menu has many options, all of which look delicious. The food comes out fast and hot. Street parking is available. Service was great. Take out service is offered. I recommend this spot to anyone in the area.

Their food is delicious, I’ll give them that; however, after years of ordering from them they’ve messed up our deliveries too many times for us to continue to be loyal customers. We’d probably still dine in though, their food is definitely good, they just need someone else to take delivery orders. Also some consistency on spice. I ordered medium spicy Noodles once and I couldn’t finish them. Keep in mind that I was raised by Mexican people who eat toasted serrano peppers as a side with their dinner. Their food is extremely tasty and well priced. Plenty of vegetarian and non-vegetarian options. I have had couple bad experiences with service when I went by myself. They keep adding an 18% service fee (which I assume is tip, however I have tipped generously based on my experience). Don't know if this is their practice with all the customers or not. Just be cautious about this. I do have to say that one of the servers over there during lunch hours is super friendly and I have had no issues when I go during those times.

Very good Thai place. Great spice to their dishes. The mild was just right for me and the medium was pretty spicy for my dining partner. Would recommend the duck dishes, pad Thai, and the noodles in soup form. Pot stickers nice and toasty too.

The food here is better than in neighbor Thai food spots, but the prices are higher too. I had here Pad Thai and duck with rice. The pad Thai was really good. But the duck on rice was frustration. This is because the lack of duck meat in my dish. There was only 20- 25% of duck meat. The rest was plain, bland rice.

Excellent food!. We ordered pad Thai, red and green curry, something with crispy noodles, chicken and crab meat. Their ice tea was awesome. Reminded us of another great restaurant in Alburquerque, NM.

Went during lunch hour, busy but was still in and out in an hour. Food was great

Loved the Indian curry rice. Added to the list of my favourite places. Will definitely keep going back for more. Had the dumplings and crab rangoon as well. They were good too. The staff is super chill and friendly. Nice place to have good food and hangout with friends.
One of the best Thai places in Chicago. Very authentic style, comparable to Bangkok or Phuket. Curry noodle bowl is a stand out dish.
Love the red curry and pad thai! Cater the spice to your liking from mild to very spicy.
Amazing food, amazing service 5 stars all the way!!!

I like spicy Indian rice

A good place and they make the food according to your flavor.

Quick and tasty. Not much seating but this gives you and your group more attention from the staff.  Great for a lunch stop, inexpensive and good size portions.

Love the fried rice.
Love the Indian curry fried rice here! A must try!

I love the food here but the delivery service and customer service at the restaurant is horrible. On Thursday, August 11, 2016 I placed an order for delivery at 11:15am. The food did not arrive until 12:45pm. It took an hour and a half to arrive. I ordered the Seafood Combination which was $12.95. The delivery fee was $3.00 and tax was $1.49. I basically paid $17.44 for one dish of food. I didn't order a drink or appetizer. It was simply one dish and they couldn't get it to me by noon. This is very appalling. When the food arrived I called to speak with the manager to ask for an explanation. They said a manager will call me back. The manager never called me. I went on their website to email them. I did and haven't gotten a response since. Customer service is the last of their priorities, so it seems. I was very disappointed because I was not able to enjoy my meal since I didn't have enough lunch time left.
Super tasty fried rice with thai green curry. Pocket friendly place to eat.
Excellent Thai food. The Indian curry fried rice and the pad see ew are especially tasty.

I love Taylor street, this is a cool place to find some street parking or valet and walk around as there is plenty to do in this little area. Usually you can find street parking just circle the block. I had the Green Curry with Chicken and an a cucumber salad. This is a BYOB establishment, so if you forget there is a 711 across the street.

My girlfriend loves this place. I do too. Its prime location on Taylor street draws a diverse crowd and is easily accessible. The food is relatively inexpensive but that doesn't hinder the quality of the dishes. You'd be insane not to buy the crab rangoon appetizer. The waitress has always been courteous and attentive to our needs. The 5/5 star rating is thoroughly deserved.
Crispy noodles recommended.
This is my favorite Thai restaurant on Taylor street.
Thumbs up to Indian Curry Fried Rice and seafood combination platter.  Try the Thai iced Coffee.
Amazing food. Especially the Chilli Paste fried rice and Indian Curry Fried rice. Special mentions to Pad Thai.

We were regular at this place for last 9 years, but lately (last 1-2 years) had to put up with inconsistent quality of the food. Mild is super hot some times and vegetables are missing in a veggi entree. If you are prepared to eat what you are served (and not what you ordered), you might be fine. Just be prepared for the unexpected, when you walk in the door. The place is dingy, hole in the wall, really cramped up, barely kept up. Like most folks, we always did take out. During our recent visit, our order was messed up once again, when we finally called up the restaurant to let him know about this, he was extremely rude, and told us that we are looking for free food. That was really hurtful to hear, and with that they lost yet another long time dedicated customer. The owner of the place, really does not care about the food, its quality or service to its long timeany of the customers.
Excellent!  Just found our new Thai place!
Amazing thai food. Basil fried rice and basil chicken are my favorites. Their panang curry and ginger chicken are really good as well.
Absolutely delicious. Great tasting thai, always spicy to your taste, and the service is rather quick. Seems like a hole in the wall place, but it's a treasure. I highly recommend coming here.
Awesome chicken pad Thai!
One of the best modest Thai restaurant i have been to with variety.
Strongly recommend "Indian Curry Fried Rice with Tofu" here.

One of my most favorite thai restaurants.  Their Pad Thai is amazing, Tom Khar is great  for when you have a cold.  Crab rangoon is lightly crispy with perfect filling to wrapper ratio.  Great delivery service and decent prices.  Highly recommended.

Try the chicken fried rice. Its the best of it's kind on Taylor street, with just the right blend of spices, onions, leeks, tomatoes, and cucumber. They make it great every time. I've been coming to this place regularly for over 5 years. The family that owns the place is courteous and attentive. I've tried their other dishes as well, but the CFR (Chicken fried rice) keep me coming back. If you can handle the heat, ordering the dish "spicy" makes it even tastier.

Wow! This place is great! Good Thai food. Best crab raggon I have had. Recommend. Chicken rice Soup, Chicken Pad Thai, Pad Won Seen "Crispy". My favorite D9 Singapore Noodles with Chicken and Shrimp. Oh and I can't forget the Thai Iced Tea. Thanks guys!!! See you soon.
